theorem Topology.closureInterior_eq_univ_of_dense_and_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (h_dense : Dense (A : Set X)) (hP1 : Topology.P1 (X:=X) A) :
    closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  -- `Dense` gives `closure A = univ`
  have h_closureA : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := h_dense.closure_eq
  -- From `P1` we get `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`
  have h_univ_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := by
    have h : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := by
      have : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := hP1
      exact closure_mono this
    simpa [h_closureA] using h
  -- The reverse inclusion is obvious
  have h_subset_univ : closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    intro x hx
    trivial
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h_subset_univ h_univ_subset

theorem Topology.interior_closure_interior_eq_interior_closure_of_isOpen {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    interior (closure (interior A)) = interior (closure A) := by
  simpa [hA.interior_eq]
